Title

User Authentication & Signup Flow

1. Introduction

This document describes the authentication workflow for new users registering on the platform. It outlines the signup process, validation rules, email verification, and error handling behavior.

2. User Signup Flow

The user navigates to the Signup page.

The user enters the following details:

Full Name

Email Address

Password

Confirm Password

The user clicks the Create Account button.

3. Validation Rules

Email address must be unique.

Email address must be in a valid format.

Password must:

Be at least 8 characters long

Contain at least one uppercase letter

Contain at least one number

Password and Confirm Password must match.

If any validation fails, the signup process is blocked and an error message is shown.

4. Successful Signup

If all validations pass, the system creates a new user account.

The user is shown a message prompting them to verify their email.

An email verification link is sent to the registered email address.

5. Email Verification Flow

User receives an email with a verification link.

User clicks the verification link.

The system verifies the token.

The user account is marked as active.

User is redirected to the login page.

6. Error Scenarios

Duplicate Email

If the email already exists, the system displays:
“Email already exists.”

Weak Password

If password rules are not met, an inline validation message is shown.

Invalid Verification Link

If the verification link is expired or invalid, the user is prompted to request a new verification email.

7. Limitations

Phone number signup is not supported.

OTP-based signup is not implemented.

CAPTCHA validation is not included.

8. Security Considerations

Passwords are stored in hashed format.

Email verification tokens expire after a fixed duration.

Multiple failed signup attempts may be rate-limited.

9. Summary

This document defines the end-to-end signup and email verification workflow. All use cases and test cases generated by the system must strictly follow the behaviors defined in this document.